Project Proposal – IS Project Management Practice
##Project Title

IS Project Management Practice

##Introduction

This project is designed to provide practical experience in planning, managing,
and collaborating on a project using modern project management tools. 
The project demonstrates how teams can effectively manage tasks, coordinate activities, 
and store project documents using digital platforms.

The tools selected for this project are Trello for task management and GitHub for file management and collaboration.

##Project Objectives

To plan and organize project activities efficiently
To assign tasks and responsibilities to team members
To track project progress using task boards
To store and manage project documents using version control
To improve collaboration and teamwork skills

##Project Scope

In Scope
Project planning and task management
Risk management and scheduling
Team collaboration
Documentation and reporting
Version control and file management

Out of Scope
Development of a full software application
Budget and cost analysis
Deployment or implementation of technical systems

##Expected Deliverables
Project Plan document
Risk Management document
Task management board
GitHub repository containing project files
Final report summarizing project outcomes

##Methodology

The project will follow a simple project management approach:

Planning Phase
   Define project scope
   Identify stakeholders
   Develop work breakdown structure (WBS)

Execution Phase
   Assign tasks and responsibilities
   Track progress through task boards
   Upload and manage files

Monitoring and Control
   Monitor progress
   Manage risks
   Track issues

Closing Phase
   Finalize documentation
   Submit final report

##Project Timeline

Phase	Timeframe
Planning-Week 1
Execution-Week 2–3
Monitoring & Control	Throughout project
Closing & Reporting-Week 4

##Conclusion

This project aims to strengthen project management skills by using collaborative tools to manage tasks,
monitor progress, and organize project files. The experience will improve teamwork, communication, 
and planning skills while demonstrating practical use of digital tools in managing projects.
